JOHANNESBURG – Hooker Malcolm Marx will return to South Africa after picking up an injury in the Lions' match against the Hurricanes in Wellington on Saturday. Marx left the field in the eighth minute of the match, which the Lions lost 28-19. READ: Lions sign new sponsor for next three years The Lions confirmed on their Twitter account that he will undergo scans on Tuesday. With the Springboks' first 2018 Test just a month away, coach Rassie Erasmus will be keeping an eye on developments. Marx is one of the few South African players who have established themselves as among the best in world rugby this season. African News Agency